Global IV Infiltration Detection Device Market Insights
IV Infiltration Detection Device Market size was valued at USD 1.2 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 2.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 10.1% from 2024 to 2030.

IV Infiltration Detection Device Market Overview
The global IV Infiltration Detection Device Market was valued at USD 331.9 million in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 479.9 million by 2032, growing at a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of 4.3% from 2024 to 2032. This growth is driven by the increasing prevalence of chronic diseases requiring long-term intravenous (IV) therapy, technological advancements enhancing detection accuracy, and a rising demand for early intervention to prevent patient discomfort and complications. The market is also experiencing a growing adoption of IV infiltration detection devices in healthcare facilities. However, challenges such as the high cost associated with advanced detection technology, limited awareness and training among healthcare professionals, and regulatory hurdles may impact market growth. North America currently holds a significant market share, with the Asia-Pacific region exhibiting rapid expansion. The wired product segment generated notable revenue in 2023, and the hospitals & clinics end-user segment holds a significant market share. The integration of artificial intelligence and machine learning for enhanced detection capabilities is a notable trend fueling industry demand.

